column5: Here's a couple of lakers from a couple of weeks ago. 1st fish hit in 85 feet of water. 2nd bigger girl hit 20 feet under the ice, over 105 FOW. I had just released a dink and started to let the jig fall back down the hole when I saw a thick red mark on my vex. I closed the bail, jigged twice and the fish slammed it! Peeled line and fought well. I think it was checking out all of the comotion with the earlier dink because she was under the hole right after I sent the small guy back. It was a high pressure day, no clouds, didn't expect anything special. Ended up icing 16 fish between the two of us. Bait shop was out of minnows, so salties tipped on tubes and spoons was on the menu.     All fished were released.
